WorkItem.ClosedComment: Thanks for the heads up!  This has already been filed as issue 11, so I'll be using that issue to track this.
WorkItem.Description:
As described on this StackOverflow question 

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12710303/should-creating-a-variable-named-this-conflict-with-this

creating a variable named `_this` after the place where the compiler would generate a `var _this` causes the new variable to overwrite the one generated by the compiler. Either `_this` should be a reserved word, or the compiler should name generated variables in a way that prevents name collisions.
WorkItem.Summary: Compiler-generated variables clash with variables declared in TypeScript
